{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 160°C. Grease and line a round cake tin (20 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Place hazelnuts into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place chocolate into mixing bowl and grate <nobr>20 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter and melt <nobr>2 min 30 sec\/80°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add sugar, baking powder, eggs, vanilla and reserved nuts and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Pour mixture into prepared tin and bake for 45-50 minutes (160°C), or until just cooked (cake will appear slightly soft in the centre). Allow to cool in tin for 15 minutes, then transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely.","Dust with maca powder (optional) before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["150 g butter, cut into pieces, plus extra for greasing (see Tips)","200 g raw hazelnuts, skins on","200 g dark chocolate, broken into pieces","150 g brown sugar (see Tips)","½ tsp baking powder","5 eggs","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","½ tsp maca powder, for dusting (optional) (see Tips)"]}],"id":"r135073","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-k0sjsbpmC-U\/XZWrxrlJc_I\/AAAAAAAAfso\/u6zdqfxnKPwjsV5lXffzE0-2YYBwZarwQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_utkkzlYt0tZvbqLr.png","title":"Simple chocolate hazelnut cake","publishedAt":"2017-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.9 g","fat":"29.7 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"20.6 g","calories":"1562 kJ \/ 371 kcal"},"usefulItems":"round cake tin (20 cm), baking paper, bowl, wire rack, oven","hintsAndTricks":["If you prefer, you can replace half of the butter with your preferred oil, such as hazelnut oil, macadamia oil or a lighter-flavoured extra virgin olive oil. Simply add the oil with the sugar and eggs.","You can use your preferred brown sugar in this cake – either regular brown sugar or a less refined option such as Rapadura sugar (Panela) or coconut sugar.","Maca is a vegetable from the brassica family and is a source of protein, fibre, iron, calcium and potassium. You can buy maca powder from some supermarkets and health food stores. It makes a nourishing alternative to icing sugar for a pretty dusted look."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 15m","12 portions"]}